4 Merge bee and moth by sampleunit

  • Predictors are from the bee dataset (not always equal to moth dataset, for example canopy.cover.nlcd, bd.kg.m3, and at least one more)

common.units <- intersect(unique(bee.big$sampleunit),unique(moth.big$sampleunit))

5 Bees - calculate NMDS

# ------------------------------
# NMDS FOR BEES
### Nonmetric Multidimensional Scaling (NDMS) ordination analysis
#filter bee.species keeping only common sampleunits
bee.species.temp <- cbind(sampleunit=bee$sampleunit,bee.species)
bee.species.temp <- bee.species.temp %>% arrange(sampleunit)
bee.species.temp <- bee.species.temp %>% filter(sampleunit %in% common.units)
dim(bee.species.temp)
## [1]  30 174
sum(bee.species.temp$sampleunit != beemoth$sampleunit)
## [1] 0
bee.species <- bee.species.temp %>% select(-sampleunit)

## Carry out an NMDS on the bee species dataframe with goal to create moth NMDS1 and NMDS2
ord<-metaMDS(bee.species,trace=F, autotransform=F,k=2, wascores = T,
             trymax = 200)
scores <- scores(ord)
## extracts site scores and puts them into an object
sitescores<-scores[["sites"]] 
dim(sitescores); colnames(sitescores)
## [1] 30  2
## [1] "NMDS1" "NMDS2"
colnames(sitescores) <- paste("bee",colnames(sitescores),sep=".")

## Add the NMDS1 and NMDS2 scores to the beemoth dataframe 
beemoth <- cbind(beemoth,sitescores)
rm(sitescores)
names(beemoth)
##  [1] "sampleunit"        "vegtype"           "priormanage"      
##  [4] "sand"              "log.area"          "openareapct"      
##  [7] "frost.free.days"   "bd.kg.m3"          "precipitation"    
## [10] "tmax"              "tmin"              "canopy.cover.nlcd"
## [13] "om"                "bee.abundance"     "bee.specnum"      
## [16] "bee.shannon"       "bee.simpson"       "moth.abundance"   
## [19] "moth.specnum"      "moth.shannon"      "moth.simpson"     
## [22] "bee.NMDS1"         "bee.NMDS2"

moth.species.temp <- moth.species.temp %>% arrange(sampleunit)
moth.species.temp <- moth.species.temp %>% filter(sampleunit %in% common.units)

             trymax = 200)

dim(sitescores); colnames(sitescores)

                 subtitle="Gold line and points are bee, blue are moth")+
            xlab(var)+
            theme_bw()
  print(p1ot)

############################################
# correlation tests
#j=1
#i=2
#counter=1

    response.vars <- c("bee.abundance","bee.specnum","bee.shannon","bee.simpson",
                     "bee.NMDS1","bee.NMDS2",
                     "moth.abundance","moth.specnum","moth.shannon","moth.simpson",
                     "moth.NMDS1","moth.NMDS2"
                     )
    
    counter <- 1
    out.rows <- choose(length(response.vars),2)
    var1 <- var2 <- r.vec <- p.value.vec <- rep(NA,out.rows)
        conf.int.mat <- matrix(rep(NA,out.rows*2),out.rows,2)
    
        for(j in 1:(length(response.vars)-1)) { 
          for(i in (j+1):length(response.vars)){
          #print(paste("j",j,"i",i))
           var1[counter] <- response.vars[j]
           var2[counter] <- response.vars[i]
           r.vec[counter] <- cor(beemoth[,response.vars[j]],beemoth[,response.vars[i]])
           p.value.vec[counter] <- cor.test(beemoth[,response.vars[j]],beemoth[,response.vars[i]])$p.value
           conf.int.mat[counter,] <- cor.test(beemoth[,response.vars[j]],beemoth[,response.vars[i]])$conf.int
          counter <- counter+1 
        }
    } 
    
        r.vec <- round(r.vec,3)
        p.value.vec <- round(p.value.vec,4)
        conf.int.mat <-round(conf.int.mat,3)
       out<- cbind(var1,var2,r.vec,p.value.vec,conf.int.mat) 
    out <- as.data.frame(out)
    names(out) <- c("Response1","Response2","r","P.value","Lower.95.ci","Upper.95.ci")
    out
